This paper is likely to belong to the category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL) as it introduces a new structure for memory neural networks and applies it to language modeling tasks. It is also likely to belong to "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) as it involves the development of a new neural network architecture. Additionally, it may belong to "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE) as it involves the use of neural networks, and "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) as the proposed architecture may have applications in image processing tasks.
